spans.content: The Manual Station Relocator is designed to lower the height of a
fire alarm pull station to meet ADA requirements. Most existing pull
floor. The Relocator lowers the height without the need for pulling
new wires and moving the existing electric box.
The Relocator is the easiest and most economical way to lower
existing pull stations. Simply remove the existing pull station from
the wall.  Connect field wiring to Relocator terminals. Reconnect
the existing (or new) pull station to wire leads on the front of the
Relocator. The Relocator is made from rugged aluminum and fin-
ished with an attractive beige finish. A large blue/white wheelchair
decal is applied to the front to clearly indicate pull station acces-
Meets physical requirements for ADA devices.
Compatible with most brands of pull stations.
The simple design ensures very fast, very easy installation.
Large terminals helps speed installation; accepts up to #12
ADA requires that pull stations be mounted 54 inches
